The paper deals with computing the von Neumann graph entropy, which is a measure of graph complexity. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category, which deals with the study of algorithms and data structures for organizing and processing information. Additionally, the paper proposes novel quadratic approximations for computing the entropy, which could fall under the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category, which deals with the study of the quantification, storage, and communication of information. The paper also conducts computational simulations on random graph models and real network datasets, which could suggest that it belongs to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category, which deals with the study of social and information networks. The paper also proposes methods to reduce the computational complexity of the entropy calculation, which could fall under the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category, which deals with the study of numerical methods for solving mathematical problems. Finally, the paper proposes novel approximations for computing the entropy, which could suggest that it belongs to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category, which deals with the study of algorithms and models for learning from data.
